  <facilityDescription><![CDATA[<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Restaurants &amp; Bars</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Gazebo Restaurant</strong> serves gourmet cuisine using the freshest seafood. It has an enviable location overlooking Alassio’s Bay and during the summer, dinner is served directly on the beach.</p>
<p><strong>GH Bistrot</strong> offers a varied menu with classic dishes like pasta or refreshing salads. The menu uses local produce and the bistrot creates a relaxing atmosphere for diners.</p>
<p><strong>Pizzeria Lentini’s</strong> serves authentic pizzas cooked in a wood-fired oven – those relaxing on the beach can even enjoy them without leaving their loungers with the exclusive food delivery service.</p>
<p><strong>GH Bar</strong> is open from 10am until late and serves cocktails alongside stunning sea views. It’s the perfect spot to watch the sun set.</p>
<p><strong>Gazebino Beach Bar</strong> is a chic bar located on Alassio’s sandy beach.</p>
<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Beach</span></strong></p>
<p>The GH Beach Club is an exclusive beach club located directly in front of the hotel on one of Liguria’s finest beaches, and guests can enjoy access to its wide range of amenities. Expect comfortable sun loungers shaded by parasols, pizza and refreshments delivered straight to your lounger (payable) and a nearby bar.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Spa</strong></span></p>
<p>Covering over 1,500 metres, the Alassio Medical Spa is one of the best in the area. Enjoy everything from pampering massages to detox programmes and a fully equipped gym. Set over three floors, this impressive spa uses Thalassotherapy with seawater collected more than 200 metres from shore to ensure its purity.</p>]]></facilityDescription>
  <familyDescription><![CDATA[<p>The hotel’s kids’ club caters for ages three to 12 years and offers a wealth of activities both within the hotel and on the beach.</p>]]></familyDescription>
